# Build outputs
build/
dist/
*.dsk
*.img
*.bin
# ...except the empty HFS template the playground patches in-browser.
# It's tiny (1.4 MB), produced once by `hfformat -l Apps`, and ships as
# a static asset so the page can hot-load apps without any backend.
!src/web/public/playground/empty-secondary.dsk
# ...and the vendored wasm-retro-cc demo binaries (committed to git so the
# playground can load them without cross-repo CI artifact downloads).
!src/web/public/precompiled/hello-toolbox.bin
!src/web/public/precompiled/hello-bare.bin
!src/web/public/precompiled/hello-initgraf.bin
!src/web/public/precompiled/hello-initgraf-local.bin

# Node
node_modules/
.env
.env.local

# Retro68 / CMake (in-source build leftovers; out-of-source build/ is
# already covered above)
CMakeCache.txt
CMakeFiles/
cmake_install.cmake
Makefile
# but our hand-written test Makefile is real source and must be tracked
!tests/unit/Makefile

# Cache for the upstream System 7.5.5 image downloaded by
# scripts/build-boot-disk.sh — never committed.
.cache/

# macOS
.DS_Store

# Test artifacts
test-results/
test-results-visual/
playwright-report/
playwright/.cache/
tests/unit/test_html_parse
tests/unit/test_weather_parse
tests/unit/test_md_parse
tests/unit/*.dSYM/

# Local AI tooling (Claude Code agent profiles, gstack, etc.) — these
# live in the working tree as developer aids and are not part of the
# project's distributable surface.
.claude/
.gstack/

# Playground sample-project seeds — copied at build time from src/app/
# by the cvm-playground-seed Vite plugin. The canonical source lives in
# src/app/<project>/, so committing these would create a second source of
# truth that's easy to forget to refresh.
src/web/public/sample-projects/

# Playground precompiled .code.bin assets — copied at build time from the
# CMake build output by the GH Actions web-build job. Same single-source-of-
# truth reasoning as sample-projects above.
src/web/public/precompiled/*.code.bin
# The vendored wasm-retro-cc demo binary (hello-toolbox.bin) and its
# provenance file (VENDORED.md) are committed to git — not rebuilt by CI.
# Everything else in precompiled/ that isn't *.code.bin is implicitly tracked.

# spike/ holds research artefacts checked out from the spike/wasm-rez
# branch for local reference. It's intentionally not part of feat/ branches.
spike/


# Playwright test-demo automation outputs (issue #71)
tests/e2e/screenshots/
test-results-test-demo/
